Front End
User Interface
Client Applications
Back End
Servers
Storage Systems
Databases
Virtual Machines
Components
Cloud Infrastructure
Management Software
Security Mechanisms
Internet Connectivity
7. Cloud Storage

Cloud storage allows data to be stored and accessed remotely through internet-connected systems.

Types
Object Storage
Block Storage
File Storage
Advantages
High availability
Scalability
Data backup and recovery
Cost efficiency
8. Cloud Security

Cloud security involves policies, technologies, and controls that protect cloud environments.

Security Measures
Encryption
Authentication
Authorization
Firewalls
Intrusion Detection Systems
Common Threats
Data Breaches
Insider Threats
Malware Attacks
Misconfiguration
9. Load Balancing

Load balancing distributes incoming network traffic across multiple servers to improve reliability and performance.

Benefits
High availability
Fault tolerance
Better performance
Scalability
Types
Round Robin
Least Connections
IP Hash
10. Containers and Microservices
Containers

Containers package applications and their dependencies into lightweight units.

Popular Tools

Docker
Kubernetes
Microservices

An architectural style where applications are built as independent, loosely coupled services.

Benefits
Easier deployment
Better scalability
Independent development
11. Serverless Computing

Serverless computing allows developers to run code without managing servers.

Features
Event-driven execution
Automatic scaling
Pay-per-use pricing
Examples
AWS Lambda
Azure Functions
Google Cloud Functions
